                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Mu'tamad fi 'l-Mu'taqad.</title>
                     <note>Front flyleaf, recto has a list of books in a good Persian hand dated 26th Decemb 1915, signature illegible. Folio after end of 7 (b): prayers in Arabic. Various obscure pencilled notes on flyleaves and doublures. Bound and uniform with Codrington/Reade omitted uncatalogued No 7 (b). Written by the same scribe. On questions of faith in Islam, from a Sunni point of view. Divided into three babs, each one of ten fasls. Headings and punctuation in red.</note>
                     <incipit>Incipit:Qala Maulana al-Sadr al-A'zam al-Imam al-Mu'azzam</incipit>
